article.headline: Lipscomb 83, Jacksonville 70
article.story: NASHVILLE, Tenn. (AP) -- Adnan Hodzic scored 20 points and three other players scored in double digits for Lipscomb as the Bisons beat Jacksonville 83-70 on Saturday. Hodzic hit eight-of-nine field goals and four-of-six free throws. Josh Slater and Eddie Ard had 17 points each for the Bisons (12-13, 6-5 Atlantic Sun Conference), while LaKory Daniels added 12. Slater also had seven rebounds. The Bisons led 40-39 at the break. They fell behind early in the second half but regained the lead, 55-53, at the 12:42 mark on a jump shot by Thomas Pfaff and held it the rest of the way. Ben Smith and Lehmon Colbert led the Dolphins (12-11, 8-3) with 18 points apiece. Lipscomb hit 20-of-30 free throws to 12-of-19 for Jacksonville.
